			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Ni-Co-Mn precursor</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">镍钴锰前体</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">NMC precursor; Ni-Co-Mn composite precursor</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">NMC precursor; Ni-Co-Mn composite precursor</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Other materials</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Ni-Co-Mn precursor is a positive electrode active material for a lithium secondary battery. It plays an important role in determining the quality of the active material NMC. The synthesis methods, such as co-precipitation, are challenging to obtain the desired precursor. The precursor powders with hollow and porous structures are prepared from the post-treatment of the as-prepared powders obtained from the aqueous spray solution. The NCM precursor is synthesized through co-precipitation reaction process using a Taylor-Couette reactor.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">镍钴锰前驱体是锂二次电池的正极活性材料。它在决定活性材料 NMC 的质量方面起着重要作用。共沉淀等合成方法很难获得所需的前驱体。具有中空和多孔结构的前驱体粉末是通过对从喷淋水溶液中获得的制备好的粉末进行后处理而制备的。NCM 前驱体是通过共沉淀反应过程使用 Taylor-Couette 反应器合成的。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Li(Ni 1/3 Co 1/3 Mn 1/3)O 2</sumFormula>
		</dataSetInformation>
